div.div:
(1) Think of the UI layer as a dumb, empty shell. Like a Mechanical Turk, it needs something else to tell it what to do in response to user events.
(2) The UI layer provides an API that can be used to manipulate it. This will be used by some sort of "application engine".
(3) All the UI layer does in response to a user action is to fire an event describing the action.
(4) The "engine" (whatever it may be) is expected to listen to this event, decide what to do and manipulate the UI using provided API function calls.
